// EmailJS credentials — public keys, safe to commit per EmailJS docs.
// Rate-limited by origin/domain, not by secrecy. Not currently wired into
// the Xcode project (synced root group + generated Info.plist make pbxproj
// edits fragile). To wire manually in Xcode:
//   1. File → Add Files → Secrets.xcconfig (do NOT add to any target)
//   2. Project → Info → Configurations → set both Debug & Release of the
//      Dino target to "Secrets" as their Based-On config
//   3. Add these keys to the generated Info.plist via Build Settings
//      INFOPLIST_KEY_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID = $(EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID)  etc.
// Until then, FeedbackService.swift uses the hardcoded fallback values
// (same as below) so the app works either way.

